[SN]TITLE[SN]
Police appeal over escaped Sandhead snake

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police have asked the public to contact them if they spot a snake which has escaped from a house in the south west of Scotland.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The King Rat snake was reported as lost from Main Street in Sandhead near Stranraer on Monday.
It is described as being about 5ft 6in long and is black with yellow bands about every three inches along its body.
The snake is not classed as venomous and poses "no threat to the public".
Police said it was likely to move towards heat.
PC Hayley Buchanan said: "Anyone coming across the snake should call Police Scotland at Stranraer on 101.
"The snake is slow moving and has a distinctive yellow dot between its eyes."
